    <section id="main">
      <div id="about" class="container page-wrap">
        <h2>About the Competition</h2>
        <p class="lead">Entries Close: <strong>Monday, 30 April 2018</strong></p>
        <p>Australian residents over 18 years of age are invited to submit their individual, original works in the following categories:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Traditional (Rhyming) Verse (max 80 lines)</li>
          <li>Free Verse (max 80 lines)</li>
          <li>Short Story (max 2000 words)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>3 prizes are being offered in each category:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>1st Prize - $1000</li>
          <li>2nd Prize - $500</li>
          <li>3rd Prize - $250</li>
        </ul>
        <p>At the judge&rsquo;s discretion, a separate <strong>Shire Resident&rsquo;s Prize of $250</strong> may be also awarded for the best entry in each category from a Shire resident not winning another prize in that category.</p>
        <p>Prizes will be awarded on <strong>Saturday, 18 August 2018</strong> at the <a href="http://shirewritersfestival.weebly.com/" target="_self">Writer's Unleashed: Sutherland Shire Writer's Festival</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <div id="entry" class="container page-wrap">
        <h2>How to Enter</h2>
        <p class="lead">Entry Fee: <strong>$15.00 per poem/story</strong></p>
        <p>The Competition is open to individuals over 18 years of age who are Australian citizens or permanent residents of Australia who are living in Australia on the day of entry. To be eligible for the&nbsp;Shire Resident&rsquo;s Prize, an entrant must
          also be living in the Sutherland Shire on the day of entry.</p>
        <p>Multiple entries from individuals are welcome but you must complete an entry form and pay the entry fee for each poem or short story you wish to submit. Entries will only be accepted online through the attached entry form. All entry fees are <strong>non-refundable</strong>.</p>
        <p>All entries must be the original work of the author. Entries must be submitted as Microsoft Word (.doc, .docx) or Rich Text Format (.rtf) files, typed in black without photographs, drawings, coloured background, illustrations or embellishments of
          any kind. To ensure impartial judging, the entrant&rsquo;s name should not appear anywhere on the poem or short story being submitted, nor in the name of the uploaded file itself.</p>
        <p>Please read the <a href="#terms">full competition Terms &amp; Conditions</a> before submitting any entries.</p>
        <p class="d-none d-sm-block"><a href="https://sutherlandshirecouncil.submittable.com/submit/17a0529f-01a7-4db7-9142-f64b672437ed/sutherland-shire-literary-competition-2018" class="btn btn-lg btn-info" target="_blank">Enter Now</a></p>
        <p class="d-block d-sm-none"><a href="https://sutherlandshirecouncil.submittable.com/submit/17a0529f-01a7-4db7-9142-f64b672437ed/sutherland-shire-literary-competition-2018" class="btn btn-lg btn-info btn-block" target="_blank">Enter Now</a></p>
